1.title: The Battle Begins...
1.plot: "The Battle Begins..." The California Arm Benders try to take down the powerhouse New York City Arms Control, led by the fiercely driven giant slayer, Mike Selearis. AMC Original.

2.title: Southern Inhospitality
2.plot: Arm wrestling guru Cobra Rhodes joins forces with the legendary Kansas City team for a battle in Louisiana against a team of outlaws and roughnecks.

3.title: The Cold War
3.plot: Everything is on the line for two fathers as the menacing squad from Erie meets the California Arm Benders at the arm wrestling table.

4.title: Bloodlines
4.plot: In Stockton, California, a crowd gathers for the arm wrestling match between the Sacramento Arm Benders and New York City Arms Control.

5.title: Welcome to the Slaughterhouse
5.plot: Bones are broken in a clash between humble farmer Nick Zinna and tactician Mike Selearis as Kansas City defends its home turf against New York.

6.title: End of the Line
6.plot: Continuing to drink, Kenny Hughes poses a serious threat to a seriously injured Nick Zinna. Cobra Rhodes and Allen Fisher renew an old rivalry.

7.title: Playing Hurt
7.plot: Mike Selearis must face Bart Wood with a broken hand. Travis Bagent reflects on how arm wrestling brought him out of poverty.

8.title: War Horse
8.plot: Arm wrestling has affected Allen Fisher's and Craig Tullier's families in different ways. Kenny and Chop receive interventions for unhealthy habits.

9.title: Battle for the Belt
9.plot: Don Underwood and Travis Bagent put a coveted championship belt on the line. Cobra contemplates what a loss to Bart Wood would mean for his career.

10.title: Final Showdown
10.plot: All the arm wrestlers travel to Los Angeles for a double-elimination tournament where rivalries and grudge matches abound.

imdb.plot outline: Game of Arms is a look inside the raw and highly competitive world of American arm wrestling. The series follows the members of five regional arm wrestling clubs in Erie, PA, Kansas City, KS, New York, NY, Sacramento, CA and Baton Rouge, LA as they hit the road and wager their reputation, relationships and money for the sport. Game of Arms not only focuses on the technique and skill in this high-stakes world, but also the family, careers and personal struggles of each man outside of the sport. Each episode features a dramatic regional match, leading to a tournament finale where the entire cast will compete for prize money and bragging rights. The series hails from Matt Renner and Ethan Prochnik, the Emmy Award-winning producers of Deadliest Catch, and executive producer Dan Ilani, their partner in Undertow Films.
